main event: A driver spotted a bright, white, circular object about 30 feet in diameter over Victorville, California in 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 3 minutes before disappearing from view.
Weather conditions were clear with unlimited ceiling and visibility at the time of the sighting.
The witness was interviewed and appeared reliable, providing a detailed description of the object.
Further analysis determined the object was likely an aircraft with distorted navigation lights due to atmospheric conditions.
There were multiple other UFO sightings reported in the Victorville area around the same time period.
sighted object: Bright, white, circular object about 30 feet in diameter
photographs: No photographs, but the report indicates 3 photographs were taken and sent for analysis
